template.name: Template macOS Content Cache
template.description: Runtime stats and storage monitoring for macOS High Sierra Caching Service.

item.name: Activated
item.description: Content Caching is enabled (true or false)

item.name: Active
item.description: Content Caching is running (true or false)

item.name: Bytes Returned to Clients
item.description: Download rate (bytes per second) to local macOS and iOS clients

item.name: Bytes Stored from Origin
item.description: Download rate (bytes per second) from Apple's app and iCloud servers

item.name: Stored: Books
item.description: Amount of data currently in cache for "Books"

item.name: Stored: iCloud
item.description: Amount of data currently in cache for "iCloud"

item.name: Stored: iOS Software
item.description: Amount of data currently in cache for "iOS Software"

item.name: Stored: macOS Software
item.description: Amount of data currently in cache for "macOS Software"

item.name: Stored: Other
item.description: Amount of data currently in cache for "Other"

item.name: Registered
item.description: Content Caching is registered with Apple's servers (true or false)

item.name: Total Cached Data Returned to Clients
item.description: Total data returned to clients from cache

item.name: Cache Hit Rate
item.description: Ratio of cached data to uncached data sent to clients as a percentage (greater than 100% is possible)

item.name: Total Stored from Origin
item.description: Total data downloaded from Apple's servers

trigger.name: macOS Content Caching service is not running on {HOST.NAME}
trigger.description: The Content Caching sharing service is not running on this macOS host.
